02/03/2008
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Criminal charges were brought Friday (February 29th) against 80 people allegedly involved in attacks on the US Embassy and other foreign missions in Belgrade last month. 
The suspects were charged with hooliganism, theft and resisting arrest. 
If convicted, each faces up to six years in prison. 
On February 21st, rioters broke into an office at the US Embassy and torched it, to demonstrate their opposition to Kosovo's independence. 
The embassies of Croatia, Slovenia, Turkey, Belgium, Germany and Bosnia and Herzegovina were also targeted. 
(RTS - 02/03/08; AP - 29/02/08)
